    {
      "id": "PopularPost213409",
      "post_content": "Spirits are a tribe that all have good evasion- either flying, unblockable, hexproof, or some combination therof.   \n  \nAlthough they aren't as powerful as, say, Specters-- they DID have a whole Block based on them in Kamigawa. They were never really going to make a good efficient Lord for either Specters or Spirits because those Tribes are- actually- just strictly more powerful (in the normal sense of the word, not in the strategic sense- please forget about tempo for a sec)- than Elves, Goblins, Merfolk, Soldiers, etc.  \n  \nI don't know off the top of my head if there is a potentially supportable Tribe in the other colors that is like Specters or Spirits- maybe Trolls for Green? But yeah- not every Tribe can have a Vampire Nocturnus. Nor should they.  \n  \n  \nThat said, it would be quite easy to make this strictly more powerful with a simple art alter:   \njust give Mace Windu's ghost back his purple lightsaber ;D  \n  \n  \n  \nEDIT: [Drogskol Captain](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Drogskol Captain), eh Wizards? Fine. I will stop making cl... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "DarthParallax",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost213409\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_post\">Spirits are a tribe that all have good evasion- either flying, unblockable, hexproof, or some combination therof. <br/><br/>Although they aren't as powerful as, say, Specters-- they DID have a whole Block based on them in Kamigawa. They were never really going to make a good efficient Lord for either Specters or Spirits because those Tribes are- actually- just strictly more powerful (in the normal sense of the word, not in the strategic sense- please forget about tempo for a sec)- than Elves, Goblins, Merfolk, Soldiers, etc.<br/><br/>I don't know off the top of my head if there is a potentially supportable Tribe in the other colors that is like Specters or Spirits- maybe Trolls for Green?  But yeah- not every Tribe can have a Vampire Nocturnus. Nor should they.<br/><br/><br/>That said, it would be quite easy to make this strictly more powerful with a simple art alter: <br/>just give Mace Windu's ghost back his purple lightsaber ;D<br/><br/><br/><br/>EDIT: <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Drogskol Captain\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Drogskol Captain\">Drogskol Captain</a>, eh Wizards? Fine. I will stop making cl... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 213409)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '213409'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                 